<script>
    // Register help content for Supplier page with pagination
    HelpPopup.register(
        'supplierManagement',
        'Supplier Management Help',
        [
            // Page 1 - Overview and Basic Features
            `
                <h4>Supplier Management - Overview</h4>
                <p>This page allows you to manage vendor information, track procurement sources, and maintain supplier records in a hierarchical tree structure.</p>

                <h5>Main Features:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Create New Supplier:</strong> Click the "+ New" button to add a new supplier or vendor group</li>
                    <li><strong>Tree Structure:</strong> Suppliers are organized in a hierarchical tree on the left panel</li>
                    <li><strong>Search Suppliers:</strong> Use the search box to find vendors by name, ID, or PAN</li>
                    <li><strong>View Supplier List:</strong> View all vendors in a sortable data grid with filtering options</li>
                    <li><strong>Edit Suppliers:</strong> Select any supplier to update their procurement and contact info</li>
                    <li><strong>Delete Suppliers:</strong> Remove inactive or duplicate supplier records</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Tree Navigation:</h5>
                <p>The left panel displays suppliers organized by groups (e.g., "Local Suppliers," "Import Vendors"). Click on any supplier to view or edit their details in the main panel.</p>

                <h5>Data Grid Features:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li>Sortable columns - Click on column headers to sort by Name, Type, or Account</li>
                    <li>Drag and drop columns to reorder your view</li>
                    <li>Search and filter vendors quickly for rapid procurement</li>
                    <li>Action buttons for Edit, Delete, and View details</li>
                </ul>
            `,

            // Page 2 - Creating New Suppliers
            `
                <h4>Creating New Suppliers</h4>

                <h5>How to Create a New Supplier:</h5>
                <ol>
                    <li>Click the "+ New" button in the top right corner</li>
                    <li>The Supplier Model form will open</li>
                    <li>Fill in the required vendor information (marked with *)</li>
                    <li>Complete all tabs with relevant procurement and tax info</li>
                    <li>Click "Save" to add the supplier to the database</li>
                </ol>

                <h5>Required Fields:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Name in English:</strong> Supplier's official registered name (Required)</li>
                    <li><strong>Type:</strong> Select supplier type (e.g., Manufacturer, Wholesaler) (Required)</li>
                    <li><strong>Permanent Address:</strong> Supplier's registered office address (Required)</li>
                    <li><strong>Account Map:</strong> Link to Accounts Payable in Chart of Accounts (Required)</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Supplier Model Tabs:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>General/Office Info:</strong> Basic vendor info and primary contact</li>
                    <li><strong>Owner/Contact:</strong> Sales rep and management contact details</li>
                    <li><strong>Location/others:</strong> Address and shipping location mapping</li>
                    <li><strong>Account/Opening Bills:</strong> Payable setup and opening balances</li>
                    <li><strong>Terms & Conditions:</strong> Credit periods and payment terms</li>
                    <li><strong>Supply Status:</strong> Categories of items supplied</li>
                    <li><strong>Purchase History:</strong> Historical pricing and order data</li>
                    <li><strong>Item Map:</strong> Map specific items to this supplier</li>
                    <li><strong>Bank Map:</strong> Supplier's bank account for electronic payments</li>
                    <li><strong>Dealer Map:</strong> Regional distributor or agent mapping</li>
                </ul>
            `,

            // Page 3 - Supplier Information Fields
            `
                <h4>Supplier Information Fields</h4>

                <h5>Basic Information:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Auto Gen.Code:</strong> System-generated vendor code</li>
                    <li><strong>Name in English:</strong> Supplier name in English (Required)</li>
                    <li><strong>In Nepali:</strong> Supplier name in Nepali language</li>
                    <li><strong>Parent:</strong> Parent supplier group (e.g., "Raw Material Vendors")</li>
                    <li><strong>Supplier Id:</strong> Unique vendor identification number</li>
                    <li><strong>Group Id:</strong> Supplier group identifier</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Supplier Types and Categories:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Under Group:</strong> Primary vendor classification</li>
                    <li><strong>Type:</strong> Supplier type selection (Required)</li>
                    <li><strong>Party Type:</strong> Business entity classification (Private, Public, etc.)</li>
                    <li><strong>Prefix/Start ID:</strong> Custom prefix for supplier numbering</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Contact Information:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Permanent Address:</strong> Official registered address (Required)</li>
                    <li><strong>Office Address:</strong> Current operational or warehouse address</li>
                    <li><strong>Tel/Mobile:</strong> Primary contact for orders</li>
                    <li><strong>Email Address:</strong> Email for Purchase Orders and Invoices</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Tax and Compliance:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>PAN/VAT No:</strong> Mandatory tax registration for legal procurement</li>
                    <li><strong>Excise No:</strong> Excise registration if purchasing regulated goods</li>
                    <li><strong>GST No:</strong> Goods and Services Tax number</li>
                    <li><strong>TIN No:</strong> Tax Identification Number</li>
                    <li><strong>IEC No:</strong> Import Export Code for foreign suppliers</li>
                </ul>
            `,

            // Page 4 - Location and Additional Details
            `
                <h4>Location and Additional Details</h4>

                <h5>Location Map:</h5>
                <p>Map the supplier's location for logistics and lead-time tracking:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>City/District:</strong> Origin of goods</li>
                    <li><strong>Region/Zone:</strong> Geographic classification</li>
                    <li><strong>Country:</strong> Required for import/customs tracking</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Procurement Assignment:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Branch Name:</strong> Assign supplier to a specific receiving branch</li>
                    <li><strong>Purchasing Officer:</strong> Assign an internal staff member to manage this vendor</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Supplier Status Flags:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Cash Supplier Y/N:</strong> Mark if payments are made immediately upon delivery</li>
                    <li><strong>Active Supplier:</strong> Enable/disable the vendor for new Purchase Orders</li>
                    <li><strong>Import Party:</strong> Mark if supplier is based outside the country</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Import Details:</h5>
                <p>For suppliers marked as Import Party, complete additional fields:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Currency - Default currency for purchases</li>
                    <li>Port of Loading - For sea/air freight tracking</li>
                    <li>IEC No. - Necessary for customs clearance documentation</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Account Mapping:</h5>
                <p><strong>Account Map (Required):</strong> Link the supplier to an "Accounts Payable" ledger. This ensures all purchase bills and payments are reflected correctly in the financial statements.</p>
            `,

            // Page 5 - Managing and Best Practices
            `
                <h4>Managing Suppliers - Best Practices</h4>

                <h5>Editing Existing Suppliers:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li>Click on supplier name in the tree or grid</li>
                    <li>Update tax or bank details in the respective tabs</li>
                    <li>Click "Save" to apply changes</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Using the Data Grid:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Sorting:</strong> Sort by "Account" to see vendors linked to specific ledgers</li>
                    <li><strong>Filtering:</strong> Filter by "Type" to quickly find manufacturers vs. retailers</li>
                    <li><strong>Actions:</strong> Use "View" to check historical balances without entering edit mode</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Best Practices:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Accurate PAN/VAT:</strong> Essential for tax input credit claims</li>
                    <li><strong>Credit Terms:</strong> Define "Terms & Conditions" to manage cash flow and payment reminders</li>
                    <li><strong>Bank Details:</strong> Maintain accurate bank info to reduce payment errors</li>
                    <li><strong>Inactive Status:</strong> Disable suppliers you no longer use instead of deleting to preserve historical data</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Important Notes:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Note:</strong> Suppliers with outstanding balances or pending POs cannot be deleted</li>
                    <li><strong>Note:</strong> Changing the "Account Map" will affect where future bills are posted</li>
                    <li><strong>Note:</strong> Ensure the "Import Party" flag is correct for proper tax calculation</li>
                </ul>
            `
        ]
    );
</script>
